# Surge 5 RULE-SET (DOMAIN-SUFFIX rules)
# Target Policy: US
# Purpose: Route Microsoft-owned consumer / productivity / developer / cloud domains through Proxy.
#
# Usage (Surge):
#   [Rule]
#   RULE-SET,https://your-domain-or-raw-link/microsoft.list,Proxy
#
# Notes:
# - Strict mode: Microsoft-owned domains only.
# - Avoids shared CDN / third-party hosts unless clearly Microsoft-owned.
# - Designed for stable, minimal-overmatch routing.

# -----------------------
# Core Microsoft / Account / Identity
# -----------------------
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,microsoft.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,microsoftonline.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,microsoftonline-p.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,live.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,live.net
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,msn.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,passport.net
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,outlook.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,office.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,office.net
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,office365.com

# -----------------------
# OneDrive / SharePoint / Teams / Collaboration
# -----------------------
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,onedrive.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,sharepoint.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,sharepointonline.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,teams.microsoft.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,skype.com

